    "long_instructions": "##Investigate and Modify\r\n\r\nExperiment with the program by making the following modifications, then run the program to observe the results.\r\n\r\n✅ TO DO: Call the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">play()</code> method with one <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">Song</code> object, then call it again with two <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">Song</code> objects, and then with three.\r\n\r\nWhat do you notice about how the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">MusicPlayer</code> class handles each call?\r\nHow does Java determine which <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">play()</code> method to run?",
